HEADWORD: Boldu
<hw>Bol"du</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A fragrant
evergreen shrub of Chili (<spn>Peumus Boldus</spn>). The bark is used in
tanning, the wood for making charcoal, the leaves in medicine, and the
drupes are eaten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

